1
00:00:10,970 --> 00:00:14,996
Please give me a big one

2
00:00:30,213 --> 00:00:36,239
As I stand here washing dishes, I want
to have sex with my wife tonight,—

3
00:00:36,279 --> 00:00:41,923
and I've been thinking since this evening
about how to make that request.

4
00:00:46,963 --> 00:00:50,223
Come on, Taro, that's enough.
Time for bed.

5
00:00:54,010 --> 00:01:00,970
For the rest of my life, I'll probably
never have sex with anyone but my wife.

6
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:04,516
Because I'm a screenwriter
who can't get work.

7
00:01:05,003 --> 00:01:09,743
I can't afford an affair,
and I can't afford a brothel.

8
00:01:10,690 --> 00:01:12,756
Hey, look, Dad!
These guys are perverts!

9
00:01:12,796 --> 00:01:14,270
Uh-huh.

10
00:01:16,250 --> 00:01:21,323
So if I want sex, for better or worse,
my wife is my only option, but—

11
00:01:21,620 --> 00:01:25,011
Doing it with my wife has somehow
become—

12
00:01:25,402 --> 00:01:28,229
a hurdle higher than the sky.

13
00:01:30,762 --> 00:01:34,530
Taro, it's past nine. Mom'll get mad
if you don't sleep. Come on.

14
00:01:34,570 --> 00:01:36,360
Hey! Don't just take it!

15
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:41,403
It's not "just." We agreed 8:30, remember?
Now brush your teeth and get to bed.

16
00:01:41,663 --> 00:01:42,990
I'm gonna say goodnight to Mom.

17
00:01:43,030 --> 00:01:49,170
No, no, don't. She'll get mad when it's past
8:30. Now where'd you put your toothbrush?

18
00:01:49,296 --> 00:01:51,596
Taro, wait!

19
00:01:54,996 --> 00:01:56,810
Mom, I'm going to bed now.

20
00:01:56,850 --> 00:02:01,310
Taro, you're still up? I told you
to be in bed by 8:30.

21
00:02:01,350 --> 00:02:06,316
Well, Dad didn't say anything,
so I didn't notice.

22
00:02:06,356 --> 00:02:08,570
Huh? Were you on your phone again?

23
00:02:08,610 --> 00:02:10,810
I was replying to a work email
and lost track of time.

24
00:02:10,850 --> 00:02:16,016
You ain't got any work. I told you
to put him to bed by 8:30.

25
00:02:16,043 --> 00:02:18,296
Taro, go to bed. Just ignore Dad.

26
00:02:18,950 --> 00:02:22,203
- Come soon, okay?
- Yeah, I'll be right there. Love you.

27
00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:26,090
- What about me?
- I don't love you.

28
00:02:27,122 --> 00:02:31,302
Just hurry up and put him to bed.
It's the only thing you're good for.

29
00:02:32,309 --> 00:02:34,070
Close the door already.

30
00:02:35,775 --> 00:02:37,356
Hurry up.

31
00:02:39,969 --> 00:02:49,463
The cat and Elmer went for a walk
in the park, wondering if there was...

32
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:52,890
Taro, forget that and listen.

33
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:56,768
Stop that. I'm not reading anymore.

34
00:02:56,808 --> 00:03:00,496
Fine, I'll stop. Can I join
the Doburock fan club then?

35
00:03:00,570 --> 00:03:03,816
I told you, only if you go
to school every day.

36
00:03:04,003 --> 00:03:06,263
Come on. Hey, listen.

37
00:03:08,020 --> 00:03:10,596
Okay. Elmer said...

38
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:22,076
Um...

39
00:03:22,371 --> 00:03:23,870
Got a minute?

40
00:03:24,593 --> 00:03:27,273
- What?
- Um, uh...

41
00:03:27,573 --> 00:03:30,460
Oh, Taro's asleep.

42
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:32,846
- So?
- Yeah.

43
00:03:33,156 --> 00:03:34,586
Uh...

44
00:03:34,983 --> 00:03:36,350
Whatcha watching?

45
00:03:36,890 --> 00:03:43,036
God, stop being annoying and don't come in.
This is my only time to relax.

46
00:03:43,570 --> 00:03:47,232
H-hey, um, so tonight...

47
00:03:47,272 --> 00:03:48,838
- No.
- Huh?

48
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:52,845
But we haven't once this month.

49
00:03:52,885 --> 00:03:57,816
Oh, shut up. How can you say that
when you neglect Taro?

50
00:03:58,250 --> 00:04:04,510
I told you sleep is crucial for kids
like him. His brain overstimulates easily.

51
00:04:04,810 --> 00:04:07,363
Putting him to bed is all you can do,
so at least do it right.

52
00:04:07,403 --> 00:04:12,820
Y-yeah. Got it. I will. I do.
So please. Just tonight.

53
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:16,216
Hey! You're seriously
pissing me off.

54
00:04:16,603 --> 00:04:20,431
Standing there just makes me hate you
more and more. Get out.

55
00:04:20,703 --> 00:04:25,150
"Just tonight"? Give me a break.
We did it last month.

56
00:04:48,216 --> 00:04:54,203
No matter how coldly she treated me,
I just wanted to quell this desire.

57
00:05:26,557 --> 00:05:28,757
Alright.

58
00:05:32,263 --> 00:05:33,732
Ta-da!

59
00:05:34,332 --> 00:05:35,931
Yay!

60
00:05:36,005 --> 00:05:37,675
Thank you.

61
00:05:40,585 --> 00:05:42,003
Here we go.

62
00:05:49,449 --> 00:05:52,383
-
Shall we have some action tonight?
-
I'm so glad to be alive.

63
00:06:18,996 --> 00:06:21,923
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife

64
00:06:22,530 --> 00:06:27,810
Episode 1:
I Don't Know How to Ask

65
00:06:39,183 --> 00:06:42,043
Hey, it's morning.

66
00:06:42,376 --> 00:06:44,656
It's 7:15.

67
00:06:44,709 --> 00:06:46,116
Come on, get up.

68
00:06:46,663 --> 00:06:50,076
- Wake up.
- Mmm... Taro.

69
00:06:50,609 --> 00:06:52,863
Come on, get up.

70
00:06:52,936 --> 00:06:54,496
Let's go to school today.

71
00:06:55,850 --> 00:06:57,416
Come on, Taro.

72
00:06:57,456 --> 00:06:58,649
Come on.

73
00:06:58,689 --> 00:07:00,883
Let's go to school today.

74
00:07:01,590 --> 00:07:03,950
Hey, asparagus is expensive.
Don't buy it.

75
00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:05,596
It's from Mexico, so...

76
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:08,076
That doesn't matter. Bean sprouts are fine.

77
00:07:09,063 --> 00:07:12,130
Chika, you always say "asparagus."
Can't you just say "aspara"?

78
00:07:12,170 --> 00:07:13,816
Shut up.

79
00:07:15,090 --> 00:07:20,470
My wife Chika works in complaint handling
at a credit card company.

80
00:07:22,156 --> 00:07:24,970
Taro, give this handout
to your teacher today, okay?

81
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:27,600
I'm putting it in here. Right here, okay?

82
00:07:29,970 --> 00:07:35,096
If it gets too hard, you can go to
the principal's office or the nurse's room.

83
00:07:35,136 --> 00:07:37,610
And if that doesn't work,
just come home.

84
00:07:38,103 --> 00:07:40,569
Going to school at all
is something to be proud of.

85
00:07:41,029 --> 00:07:42,505
OK? Good.

86
00:07:42,562 --> 00:07:46,495
- Alright, put your backpack on.
-
Our son has been reluctant to go to school.

87
00:07:46,808 --> 00:07:48,563
- There we go.
- Mama... I don't wanna.

88
00:07:48,603 --> 00:07:49,935
There, there. You're so brave.

89
00:07:49,975 --> 00:07:53,730
Honestly, I want to bury
my face in that chest too.

90
00:07:53,783 --> 00:07:57,696
Okay! Now off you go.
Mommy needs to get ready too.

91
00:07:58,483 --> 00:08:00,776
- We're off!
- Bye, have a good day!

92
00:08:08,436 --> 00:08:11,236
Taro, can we walk
a little faster?

93
00:08:22,123 --> 00:08:24,770
Come on. Can't do it?

94
00:08:25,623 --> 00:08:28,170
You haven't gone to school
once this week.

95
00:08:29,156 --> 00:08:30,543
Hey, let's try, okay?

96
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:47,550
So it didn't work out.

97
00:08:47,650 --> 00:08:50,123
Yeah. He froze up.

98
00:08:50,970 --> 00:08:52,516
I see.

99
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:55,256
Well, can't be helped.

100
00:08:55,903 --> 00:09:00,283
Taro, half your usual games and iPad.
Only after homework's done.

101
00:09:01,476 --> 00:09:02,802
Okay?

102
00:09:02,870 --> 00:09:04,630
Mommy's heading to work now.

103
00:09:05,255 --> 00:09:06,622
Okay. See you.

104
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,236
- Yeah.
- Bye.

105
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:10,636
- Have a good day.
- I'm off.

106
00:09:13,416 --> 00:09:16,889
This is a typical morning
in the Yanagida household.

107
00:09:37,456 --> 00:09:39,156
Done! Can I use the iPad?

108
00:09:39,183 --> 00:09:44,776
Huh? Write more neatly.
You don't wanna redo it, right?

109
00:09:44,816 --> 00:09:46,303
Yeah. Can I use the iPad?

110
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:49,096
Are you listening?
Write more neatly.

111
00:09:49,136 --> 00:09:50,788
Fine, fine! Can I use the iPad?

112
00:09:50,828 --> 00:09:54,730
No, you don't get it.
Write all of these five more times.

113
00:09:54,770 --> 00:09:56,376
Why? No way, no!

114
00:09:56,560 --> 00:10:00,941
Don't give me that. Write them all
or no iPad and no games.

115
00:10:00,981 --> 00:10:04,380
But Papa, you always let me!
No, no, no!

116
00:10:04,420 --> 00:10:08,436
I said no. Fine, nothing for you then.
That's it.

117
00:10:08,666 --> 00:10:10,286
Papa's gonna go work over there.

118
00:10:19,656 --> 00:10:22,269
Not that I have much work to do.

119
00:10:22,790 --> 00:10:25,550
Locked in a daily battle
with my truant son,

120
00:10:25,755 --> 00:10:30,936
I spend my days sighing over
my peers' success on social media.

121
00:10:31,569 --> 00:10:33,262
Producer Sasaki

122
00:10:36,603 --> 00:10:40,550
- Hello?
- Hey there, Yanagida!

123
00:10:41,236 --> 00:10:45,003
Long time no talk.
How are you? You busy?

124
00:10:45,443 --> 00:10:48,433
It's been a while.
Right now, you mean?

125
00:10:48,860 --> 00:10:53,966
No, I don't mean this very second.
I mean lately.

126
00:10:54,160 --> 00:11:01,176
God, when I say "now," idiots always
think I mean this instant. Like you.

127
00:11:03,103 --> 00:11:05,943
Well, I'm getting by, sort of.

128
00:11:06,486 --> 00:11:11,609
Oh, you're busy then?
Guess it won't work out.

129
00:11:12,470 --> 00:11:16,288
It's a reenactment gig.
A medical one.

130
00:11:16,328 --> 00:11:21,341
You know, like the one you did before.
Your wife came to the meeting too.

131
00:11:21,655 --> 00:11:23,356
Oh,

132
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:25,728
Wait, did your wife write it?

133
00:11:25,783 --> 00:11:28,563
No no no, she just helped out a bit.

134
00:11:28,630 --> 00:11:31,756
Um, let me check my schedule.

135
00:11:32,130 --> 00:11:33,923
Sure.

136
00:11:37,323 --> 00:11:41,510
Well, I could probably
make it work, so...

137
00:11:42,250 --> 00:11:44,696
Yes. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

138
00:11:45,569 --> 00:11:47,930
Okay, I'll wait for your call. Yes.

139
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:51,030
Thank you. Talk soon.

140
00:11:54,596 --> 00:11:56,395
As if he's busy.

141
00:11:57,143 --> 00:12:02,236
Even a crappy reenactment gig from
a flaky producer makes me happy.

142
00:12:02,843 --> 00:12:05,883
If I get work,
Chika might be in a better mood.

143
00:12:06,163 --> 00:12:09,710
And maybe I can use it as leverage
to get sex tonight.

144
00:12:13,003 --> 00:12:15,383
Eight years and two months ago

145
00:12:20,536 --> 00:12:25,608
Hey. Moan all you want, but I'm giving
you all this action, so get it together.

146
00:12:25,648 --> 00:12:27,383
- Yeah.
- You're not untalented.

147
00:12:27,423 --> 00:12:31,623
Yeah. I'll try harder.
So just a little more action...

148
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:35,403
How much do you love this stuff?
I'll bite it off.

149
00:12:51,803 --> 00:12:56,630
Taro. Taro. Taro.

150
00:12:57,343 --> 00:13:03,156
Okay, that's enough. But next time
you get one wrong, write it five times.

151
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:07,983
Got it? If you do,
I'll let you use the iPad.

152
00:13:08,230 --> 00:13:09,990
- Got it.
- Good.

153
00:13:11,099 --> 00:13:14,906
Daddy's gonna work over there,
so watch it here, okay?

154
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:16,331
Okay. Good luck with work!

155
00:13:16,371 --> 00:13:18,443
Yeah, yeah. I'll do my best.

156
00:13:18,610 --> 00:13:21,070
And don't come in, okay?

157
00:13:21,723 --> 00:13:27,089
Also, watch something besides Doburock.
Like Ghibli or something.

158
00:14:11,443 --> 00:14:13,473
Taro, be careful.

159
00:14:15,143 --> 00:14:16,676
Taro.

160
00:14:20,810 --> 00:14:22,970
Coming!

161
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:24,556
- I'll get the door.
- Hi there.

162
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:26,820
- Hello!
- Hello, Taro!

163
00:14:26,860 --> 00:14:28,903
- Hello.
- Come in!

164
00:14:31,393 --> 00:14:34,366
Sunflower
Developmental Support School

165
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,500
Okay, let's all think about this together.

166
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:43,238
A boy named Kenta really didn't want
to be "it" in a game of tag,

167
00:14:43,278 --> 00:14:46,340
but he ended up being "it"
and got really angry.

168
00:14:46,645 --> 00:14:49,300
How angry do you think Kenta got?

169
00:14:49,505 --> 00:14:51,650
Try putting yourself in his shoes.

170
00:14:51,690 --> 00:14:58,508
Five, five! Definitely five!
One! Two! One, one! Five, five!

171
00:14:58,548 --> 00:15:00,288
Everyone has a different answer.

172
00:15:00,328 --> 00:15:04,748
- Definitely five, five!
- So what should you do when you hit a five?

173
00:15:04,788 --> 00:15:06,175
Punch them. Hit them.

174
00:15:06,215 --> 00:15:07,768
- No no, you can't hit.
- Kick them.

175
00:15:07,808 --> 00:15:09,981
No kicking either.
There are other ways, right?

176
00:15:10,021 --> 00:15:11,835
- Run away. Jump.
- Take deep breaths.

177
00:15:11,875 --> 00:15:15,016
- Jump around, run away.
- Nice, deep breaths is a great idea.

178
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:21,565
Now that I've got work coming in,
if I cook Chika's favorite food...

179
00:15:22,096 --> 00:15:25,636
the hurdle to sex
might be that much lower.

180
00:15:26,070 --> 00:15:27,408
Oh, hey, Go!

181
00:15:27,448 --> 00:15:28,863
Oh, hey, Midori!

182
00:15:28,903 --> 00:15:31,416
Mina, you've gotten so big!

183
00:15:31,456 --> 00:15:35,368
- Where's Taro?
- He's at Sunflower. A spot finally opened.

184
00:15:35,408 --> 00:15:36,808
Oh, nice!

185
00:15:36,848 --> 00:15:40,735
Too bad, Mina. We were just talking
at home about how Taro's doing.

186
00:15:40,775 --> 00:15:42,481
Let's hang out again!

187
00:15:42,521 --> 00:15:45,023
- I'm gonna go look at snacks.
- Okay, just one!

188
00:15:47,063 --> 00:15:50,200
She's really gotten big, huh?

189
00:15:51,030 --> 00:15:52,248
Takes after her dad, maybe?

190
00:15:52,288 --> 00:15:53,348
Olympics-bound, then!

191
00:15:53,388 --> 00:15:56,900
Maybe so. She just won first place
in a marathon the other day.

192
00:15:56,950 --> 00:15:58,528
How about Taro?
Is he going to school?

193
00:15:58,568 --> 00:16:02,508
Well, maybe once or twice a week.

194
00:16:02,548 --> 00:16:08,176
That's plenty! I barely went
starting in middle school and I'm fine.

195
00:16:08,776 --> 00:16:14,836
Oh, come by the children's cafeteria again!
The moms love your cooking, Go.

196
00:16:14,896 --> 00:16:16,988
For sure! I've got
new recipes too.

197
00:16:17,028 --> 00:16:21,688
Ooh, let's swap dirty stories again.
Have you fixed the sexless thing?

198
00:16:21,728 --> 00:16:23,357
Nope, not at all.

199
00:16:23,397 --> 00:16:25,010
What about you guys?

200
00:16:25,050 --> 00:16:32,063
Total disaster. It's over. He pisses me off.
I set the mood and everything!

201
00:16:32,386 --> 00:16:39,863
Today we used the anger thermometer
to explore our feelings and imagine others'.

202
00:16:39,996 --> 00:16:45,055
We hope to nurture empathy and social skills
through enjoying activities together.

203
00:16:45,095 --> 00:16:46,957
Thank you.

204
00:16:46,997 --> 00:16:49,955
- Come on, let's go, let's go.
- See you next time, Taro!

205
00:16:49,995 --> 00:16:51,230
- Bye-bye!
- Be careful!

206
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:53,580
Goodbye!

207
00:16:54,303 --> 00:16:56,696
- See you, Taro!
- Okay!

208
00:16:59,716 --> 00:17:04,134
Dad, I taught everyone about Doburock!
Some didn't even know them. Unbelievable!

209
00:17:04,174 --> 00:17:09,640
Uh-huh. But did you listen to your friends?
You can't just talk the whole time.

210
00:17:11,277 --> 00:17:21,283
So please... Give me a big one,
give me a huge one

211
00:17:21,683 --> 00:17:23,493
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

212
00:17:24,090 --> 00:17:31,982
Give me one bigger than
a bridge crossing a mighty river

213
00:17:32,022 --> 00:17:39,743
Give me a big one, bigger than...

214
00:17:46,423 --> 00:17:50,674
Taro, watch other videos sometimes.
Not just Doburock.

215
00:17:50,714 --> 00:17:52,761
- Yeah.
- Ghibli movies are great too.

216
00:17:52,801 --> 00:17:56,030
- Yeah.
- Hey, can you help set out the chopsticks?

217
00:17:56,070 --> 00:17:57,643
Okay.

218
00:17:58,770 --> 00:18:00,320
I'm home.

219
00:18:00,896 --> 00:18:02,421
Mommy's home.

220
00:18:02,461 --> 00:18:05,708
Welcome back!
Tonight's acqua pazza.

221
00:18:05,748 --> 00:18:08,634
What? How much did that cost?

222
00:18:08,674 --> 00:18:14,512
Oh, well, I got work for the first time
in a while. Not exactly celebrating, but...

223
00:18:14,552 --> 00:18:17,979
Remember that medical reenactment drama
I did before?

224
00:18:18,019 --> 00:18:22,940
Seriously? That gig's amazing.
Good pay for like 30 minutes of work.

225
00:18:24,369 --> 00:18:28,223
Wait, what are you saying?
I wrote most of that.

226
00:18:28,316 --> 00:18:31,703
You said you couldn't understand the doctor
jargon and dumped it all on me. Move over.

227
00:18:31,743 --> 00:18:36,176
I wouldn't say "dumped"...
You offered to write it, Chika.

228
00:18:36,216 --> 00:18:39,497
'Cause you were gonna bail on it otherwise!

229
00:18:39,683 --> 00:18:43,255
Why did I have to pretend to be
your assistant at the meetings?

230
00:18:43,295 --> 00:18:45,840
God, now I'm getting pissed off again.

231
00:18:46,026 --> 00:18:48,860
And it's ridiculous that you even
had an assistant in the first place.

232
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:50,920
Let's not dig up ancient history.

233
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:52,365
Ancient? That was last year!

234
00:18:52,405 --> 00:18:54,418
No, I'll do it right this time.

235
00:18:54,458 --> 00:18:58,231
Back then, how do I put it...
my brain just wasn't working right.

236
00:18:58,271 --> 00:19:00,403
When have things ever been going well?!

237
00:19:00,443 --> 00:19:03,181
But you had fun writing it too, Chika.

238
00:19:03,221 --> 00:19:11,080
I did not! Writing every single night
after work— I was losing my hair!

239
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:15,310
Move!

240
00:19:15,496 --> 00:19:19,260
Taro, I'm home.

241
00:19:19,723 --> 00:19:21,248
How was Himawari today?

242
00:19:21,288 --> 00:19:22,756
Yeah, it was fun.

243
00:19:22,796 --> 00:19:25,120
It was? That's great!

244
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:28,476
But Mama, it's sad when you say that
while staring at your iPad.

245
00:19:28,516 --> 00:19:32,970
Today you practiced reading expressions
using the anger thermometer, right?

246
00:19:33,010 --> 00:19:34,555
Anger thermometer?

247
00:19:34,595 --> 00:19:36,800
- What's that? Tell me.
- Later.

248
00:19:37,449 --> 00:19:39,616
Okay. Tell me later then.

249
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:45,290
Anyway, I got some work coming in,
so let's splurge a little.

250
00:19:45,330 --> 00:19:47,976
Oh right, I ran into Midori.

251
00:19:48,016 --> 00:19:53,776
She invited me to the children's
cafeteria again. My cooking was a hit.

252
00:19:53,816 --> 00:19:56,490
Whatever. Just go if you want.

253
00:19:56,530 --> 00:19:59,790
You're just gonna show off
what a great dad you are anyway.

254
00:20:00,130 --> 00:20:04,501
Just so you know, the other moms
are totally put off by your need for praise.

255
00:20:04,541 --> 00:20:07,740
No, I don't have some need
for praise or anything...

256
00:20:07,780 --> 00:20:10,920
Take that away from you
and what's even left?

257
00:20:14,743 --> 00:20:17,100
Why are you grinning?
You're creeping me out.

258
00:20:17,296 --> 00:20:19,633
What? What do you mean?

259
00:20:20,136 --> 00:20:21,900
Don't "what" me.

260
00:20:22,156 --> 00:20:27,006
And just so we're clear, it ain't happening.
I can tell you're scheming something gross.

261
00:20:27,046 --> 00:20:29,328
Well, you know, things may
naturally lead to...

262
00:20:29,368 --> 00:20:31,240
Nothing's "leading" anywhere.

263
00:20:32,236 --> 00:20:33,636
What are you watching, Taro?

264
00:20:33,676 --> 00:20:35,528
Huh? What's leading where?

265
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:38,776
Nothing. Your dad's
just being gross.

266
00:20:38,816 --> 00:20:45,030
Okay! Let's eat, let's eat!
It's acqua pazza! Here you go.

267
00:20:45,070 --> 00:20:49,169
Wow, smells great!
Come on, come on!

268
00:20:49,209 --> 00:20:52,201
- Here.
- Are you watching this again?

269
00:20:52,241 --> 00:20:55,335
- You really love this, Taro.
- Okay, opening up... ta-da!

270
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:57,098
- Wow!
- What even is acqua pazza?

271
00:20:57,138 --> 00:20:59,416
Ahh, smells amazing.

272
00:21:05,173 --> 00:21:06,405
Excuse me...

273
00:21:06,445 --> 00:21:07,830
Don't "excuse me" me.

274
00:21:07,870 --> 00:21:12,628
Um, are you sure tonight's a no-go?
I'll throw in a massage.

275
00:21:12,668 --> 00:21:14,750
No. You suck at massages anyway.

276
00:21:14,790 --> 00:21:21,793
But I finally got work, and I'll try harder.
I won't dump everything on you this time.

277
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:24,488
No kidding. It's your job, ain't it?

278
00:21:24,528 --> 00:21:26,940
So please. Just tonight.

279
00:21:27,270 --> 00:21:30,280
"Just"? It's never "just," is it?

280
00:21:30,914 --> 00:21:32,800
I'm on my period, so no.

281
00:21:33,359 --> 00:21:34,639
Huh?

282
00:21:34,726 --> 00:21:36,026
What?

283
00:21:36,512 --> 00:21:37,938
Really?

284
00:21:38,612 --> 00:21:41,852
What's with that tone? You doubting me?
Seriously? Want me to show you proof?

285
00:21:41,892 --> 00:21:44,043
No, no... okay, fine.

286
00:21:44,293 --> 00:21:46,633
Then, when your period's over...

287
00:21:46,727 --> 00:21:49,416
Give it a rest. It's never ending.

288
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:52,316
Go put Taro to bed already.

289
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:12,630
I no longer had any idea how to ask
in order to have sex with my wife.

290
00:22:14,562 --> 00:22:15,563
Next Episode Preview

291
00:22:15,603 --> 00:22:18,215
Can't I even say no
to my husband wanting sex?

292
00:22:18,255 --> 00:22:20,513
Can't a guy even ask
his own wife for sex?

293
00:22:20,553 --> 00:22:22,164
I got a friends-with-benefits thing going.

294
00:22:22,204 --> 00:22:23,605
Why don't you
just sign up for one?

295
00:22:23,645 --> 00:22:25,833
Don't send me that crap
message while I'm at work.

296
00:22:25,873 --> 00:22:27,651
If I call the cops,
you're getting arrested.

297
00:22:27,691 --> 00:22:29,866
No, come on...
